Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.57,0:16:13.54,Default,Narrator,0,0,0,,centered around Tokyu Department Store's Toyoko Outlet,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.54,0:16:18.21,Default,Narrator,0,0,0,,a Veil with a radius of approximately 400 meters was cast.
Comment: 0,0:16:23.96,0:16:24.00,Default,chptr,0,0,0,,{Part B}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.89,0:16:37.68,Default,Men,0,0,0,,{\an8}Drink, drink, drink, drink!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.68,0:16:39.69,Default,Men,0,0,0,,{\an8}Yay, yay, yay, yay!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.19,0:16:39.69,Default,Men,0,0,0,,Hurry it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.69,0:16:41.36,Default,Men,0,0,0,,Cut it out, idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.86,0:16:46.61,Default,Youth,0,0,0,,I heard a buncha people from\N Ibaraki and Tochigi come in for Halloween.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.61,0:16:47.78,Default,Youth,0,0,0,,From way out there?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.78,0:16:49.36,Default,Man,0,0,0,,Excuse me, ladies!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.36,0:16:50.99,Default,Man,0,0,0,,Mind if we take a pic?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.99,0:16:52.74,Default,Man,0,0,0,,You look {\i1}real{\i0} cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.74,0:16:54.83,Default,Woman,0,0,0,,{\pos(480,1020)}Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.03,0:16:54.83,Default,Woman,0,0,0,,{\pos(1200,1020)}Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.87,0:16:54.83,Default,Woman,0,0,0,,{\pos(850,1020)}Gladly!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.25,0:16:59.37,Default,Youth,0,0,0,,Way to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.37,0:17:01.83,Default,Youth,0,0,0,,Let's not do Shibuya again next year.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.84,0:17:05.13,Default,Youth,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.13,0:17:06.59,Default,Youth,0,0,0,,Hm? What's what?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.59,0:17:08.30,Default,Youth,0,0,0,,That thing up there!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.01,0:17:12.97,Default,Youth,0,0,0,,What? I don't see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.64,0:17:15.64,Default,Youth,0,0,0,,Dude, it's like, right there!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.64,0:17:17.81,Default,Youth,0,0,0,,Are you blind?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.74,0:17:32.20,Default,Youth,0,0,0,,What're you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.20,0:17:33.20,Default,Youth,0,0,0,,What a clown!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.20,0:17:34.91,Default,Youth,0,0,0,,You drunk already?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.91,0:17:36.24,Default,Youth,0,0,0,,It's too early for that!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.24,0:17:38.95,Default,Youth,0,0,0,,No, there's an invisible wall here! I swear!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.27,0:18:10.40,Default,Ijichi,0,0,0,,{\an8}It's a Veil that traps only civilians inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.40,0:18:12.28,Default,Ijichi,0,0,0,,{\an8}They can enter it but not leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.28,0:18:14.11,Default,Ijichi,0,0,0,,{\an8}As for windows, it depends.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.11,0:18:18.87,Default,Ijichi,0,0,0,,Sorcerers and assistant supervisors\N seem to have no trouble moving in and out.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.87,0:18:20.12,Default,Nanami,0,0,0,,Any reception?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.12,0:18:21.41,Default,Ijichi,0,0,0,,It's blocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.41,0:18:26.88,Default,Ijichi,0,0,0,,All communication will have to be done \Noutside the Veil, through us assistant supervisors.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.88,0:18:29.76,Default,Nanami,0,0,0,,{\an8}Well, that's awfully inconvenient.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.76,0:18:31.76,Default,Ino,0,0,0,,Fushiguro! Fushiguro!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.76,0:18:33.26,Default,Ino,0,0,0,,Here's a fun fact!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.26,0:18:39.89,Default,Ino,0,0,0,,The conditions of a Veil can only be defined\N in terms of "things with cursed energy."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.89,0:18:43.64,Default,Ino,0,0,0,,That includes humans,\N cursed spirits, and cursed objects. {possible to switch the curses and cursed spirits icon in the video?}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.64,0:18:48.11,Default,Ino,0,0,0,,Blocking cell phone reception is just\N a side effect of the Veil.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.11,0:18:52.90,Default,Ino,0,0,0,,You can't actually block or allow reception\Nusing barrier techniques.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.70,0:18:55.70,Default,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,Um, yes. I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.11,0:18:58.74,Default,Nanami,0,0,0,,Ino{**-kun}, he's an exceptionally talented student.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.74,0:19:00.20,Default,Nanami,0,0,0,,Keep the senior act in check.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.20,0:19:02.83,Default,Ino,0,0,0,,What's that supposed to mean, {*}Mr. Nanami{*Nanami-san}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.12,0:19:05.87,Default,Nanami,0,0,0,,Lastly, where is Gojo{**-san}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.75,0:19:10.88,Default,Kugisaki,0,0,0,,{\an8}The Shibuya Scramble is empty? How is this real?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.88,0:19:12.88,Default,Kugisaki,0,0,0,,We're talking Shibuya on Halloween!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.88,0:19:15.76,Default,Nitta,0,0,0,,It would seem something has happened there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.76,0:19:20.39,Default,Nitta,0,0,0,,Everyone's running to the edge of the Veil,\N shouting the same thing:
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.22,0:19:24.52,Default,Nitta,0,0,0,,"Bring Gojo Satoru."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.56,0:19:28.98,Default,Naobito,0,0,0,,{\an8}Non-sorcerers couldn't possibly know his name.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.98,0:19:30.52,Default,Naobito,0,0,0,,{\an8}They were forced to say it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.02,0:19:33.19,Default,Naobito,0,0,0,,Can we not just break the Veil? {wtf is that sfx}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.53,0:19:35.24,Default,Nitta,0,0,0,,We're having a hard time with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.24,0:19:39.20,Default,Nitta,0,0,0,,Sorcerers don't feel any resistance from either side.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.83,0:19:42.74,Default,Nitta,0,0,0,,So we can't just break it by force.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.74,0:19:46.92,Default,Nitta,0,0,0,,It'll be faster to locate and neutralize\N the curse user who lowered it. {She used "lower" in the first season.} {oh good catch}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.46,0:19:49.92,Default,Maki,0,0,0,,And we're here to help out with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.42,0:19:51.34,Default,Nitta,0,0,0,,Actually, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.34,0:19:53.80,Default,Nitta,0,0,0,,You all are to wait here on standby!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.17,0:20:00.47,Default,Kusakabe,0,0,0,,{\an8}They deployed an advanced barrier technique\N and called out Gojo Satoru specifically. {An advanced barrier while calling out Gojo Satoru specifically.}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.47,0:20:04.18,Default,Kusakabe,0,0,0,,{\an8}Sounds like the same group who attacked\N the exchange event.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.18,0:20:06.81,Default,Kusakabe,0,0,0,,{\an8}The upper brass wants to minimize casualties,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.81,0:20:11.57,Default,Kusakabe,0,0,0,,{\an8}so they've decided to send Gojo Satoru in alone to deal with the situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.07,0:20:18.07,Default,Kusakabe,0,0,0,,{\an8}Us, Nanami, Zenin's old man, and Mei Mei.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.07,0:20:23.79,Default,Kusakabe,0,0,0,,{\an8}We're all here on standby outside the Veil\N to catch any of Gojo's rebounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.79,0:20:26.66,Default,Kusakabe,0,0,0,,{\an8}'Cause we can't stay in contact if we're inside. {what happened to his accent from the movie smh}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.21,0:20:31.42,Default,Panda,0,0,0,,By "minimize casualties,"\N they only mean sorcerer casualties, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.42,0:20:34.42,Default,Panda,0,0,0,,What about the civilians?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.42,0:20:36.67,Default,Kusakabe,0,0,0,,Don't get bristly with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.67,0:20:41.30,Default,Kusakabe,0,0,0,,Unlike last year's Night Parade of a Hundred Demons\N on Christmas, events are already in motion.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.30,0:20:43.43,Default,Kusakabe,0,0,0,,I think this was the best call, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.43,0:20:48.56,Default,Kusakabe,0,0,0,,Besides, I had a peek inside the Veil earlier,\N and it was pretty peaceful.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.56,0:20:53.94,Default,Kusakabe,0,0,0,,People were panicking, sure, but I didn't see any\N cursed spirits or curse users going around killing them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.94,0:20:57.32,Default,Kusakabe,0,0,0,,They're just trapped inside, as of now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.99,0:21:01.41,Default,Kusakabe,0,0,0,,Though, honestly, I don't wanna go back inside again.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.41,0:21:02.45,Default,Panda,0,0,0,,Why's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.91,0:21:05.87,Default,Kusakabe,0,0,0,,It was around Hikarie, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.83,0:21:10.79,Default,Kusakabe,0,0,0,,{\an8}I sensed a bunch of special-grade curses underground.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.75,0:21:13.17,Default,RegularPeople,0,0,0,,What's going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.17,0:21:14.88,Default,RegularPeople,0,0,0,,Why can't we pass through?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.88,0:21:17.59,Default,Youth,0,0,0,,Hurry up and bring Gojo Satoru!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.59,0:21:19.13,Default,Youth,0,0,0,,Who's this Gojo, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.63,0:21:20.97,Default,Youth,0,0,0,,Hell if I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.97,0:21:23.51,Default,Youth,0,0,0,,They just said we can't get out \Nunless he comes here!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.51,0:21:24.39,Default,Youth,0,0,0,,Who said?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.39,0:21:26.31,Default,Youth,0,0,0,,I dunno! I just heard!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.31,0:21:29.43,Default,Youth,0,0,0,,Get a load of this guy\N losing his cool at a time like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.43,0:21:32.69,Default,Youth,0,0,0,,Honestly, being trapped {\i1}is{\i0} something\N out of a horror movie,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.69,0:21:34.73,Default,Youth,0,0,0,,but it can't be {\i1}that{\i0} bad, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.73,0:21:36.36,Default,Youth,0,0,0,,I'm sure help will come soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.36,0:21:38.40,Default,Youth,0,0,0,,Oh, but we've got no reception.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.69,0:21:41.07,Default,Youth,0,0,0,,Did y'all not see it earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.45,0:21:43.03,Default,Youth,0,0,0,,They were sucked in.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.03,0:21:45.58,Default,Youth,0,0,0,,All those people at the intersection.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.58,0:21:47.37,Default,Youth,0,0,0,,Sucked right into the station!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.37,0:21:49.96,Default,Youth,0,0,0,,Like water down the drain!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.25,0:21:53.33,Default,Youth,0,0,0,,If it wasn't for that, I'd be on the train home!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.33,0:21:55.84,Default,Youth,0,0,0,,Use your brain a little, you dumb fucks! {based cr}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.84,0:21:56.80,Default,Youth,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.80,0:21:59.38,Default,Youth,0,0,0,,Then why don't you use\N that {\i1}brain{\i0} of yours to pass through?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.80,0:22:02.13,Default,Youth,0,0,0,,Ow.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.60,0:22:06.93,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,Oh, sorry.
Comment: 0,0:22:09.98,0:22:10.02,Default,chptr,0,0,0,,{Ending}
Comment: 0,0:23:39.98,0:23:40.02,Default,chptr,0,0,0,,{Preview}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.86,0:23:44.53,Default,Kugisaki,0,0,0,,{\an8}I asked for pineapple bread, so why the heck did ya get\N choco chip pineapple bread?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.53,0:23:46.61,Default,Itadori,0,0,0,,{\an8}Cuz pineapple bread with choco chips goes hard!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.61,0:23:48.49,Default,Kugisaki,0,0,0,,{\an8}They go as hard as Kanpura with Gunpla!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.49,0:23:49.70,Default,Itadori,0,0,0,,{\an8}Wait, what's a Kanpura?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.70,0:23:50.33,Default,Kugisaki,0,0,0,,{\an8}Oops. {kugasaki goes into country-girl mode when she's angry, and this time she says choco chips with pinapple bread is as good as kanpura with gunpla, where kanpura is the name of a boiled potato dish from the countryside.}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.33,0:23:51.58,Default,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,{\an8}Next time, The Shibuya Incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.58,0:23:52.87,Default,Kugisaki,0,0,0,,{\an8}You know what it is, right, Fushiguro?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.87,0:23:54.62,Default,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,{\an8}I've made Acguy before. {acguy/aggai is a pun on "aka" which means red, as in the red sauce that the kanpura dish is usually eaten with} {why would fushiguro know about this? im guessing it's because he COOKS so he might've tried to make this dish}
